:

At WSP, there’s nothing we love more than pushing boundaries. Harnessing innovation and sharing insights across our diverse, international team to create a tomorrow’s world that's cleaner, greener and safer. Join us and you’ll be part of an organisation that takes pride in its people and purpose: creating long-lasting solutions to meet the needs of generations to come.

We are seeking a Geospatial Data Scientist to join our Smart Consulting team at a senior level, this would suit someone with experience in the geospatial domain.

A typical week would include:
Application of advanced analysis techniques to promote and implement solutions for existing projects and research/develop new technologies and solutions;
Development of methodologies, analysis and tools for external clients as well as a focus on the internal business to drive efficiencies and innovation;
Designing and implementing automated workflows to drive efficiency and resilience;
Close working with our software development team to instil forward thinking spatial data analysis and dynamic visualisation;
Deliver thought leadership to promote service offerings and generate new business;
Providing input to business development and work winning activities;
Willingness to share technical knowledge, engage in mentoring and foster collaboration across all levels of the team;
Acting as a key technical contact for queries from outside of the team within the wider business.

We'd love to hear from you if you have:
Extensive experience ideally gained in a consultancy environment, with Transport sector knowledge preferred;
A tertiary degree (at 2:1 or above) in Geomatics, GIS, Spatial Data Science or related field of expertise is essential with an MSc being preferable;
Significant and current technical knowledge of advanced spatial and statistical analysis to deliver insight from data;
Evidence of previous thought leadership, ideally with an existing market presence;
A balanced view of proprietary and open source spatial technology solutions to meet differing client requirements;
Experience of cloud based and distributed data computing;
Advanced coding skills in either Python or R and strong SQL skills (experience with PostgreSQL preferred);
Comfortable on the command line in Windows and Linux environments;
Knowledge of dynamic data visualisation (Javascript, Tableau, PowerBI);
Knowledge of toolsets for Big Data analysis and when to use them (Hadoop, Apache Spark, MapD, RAPIDS AI, Dask);
Commercial and business development experience.

